⚠️ shallow (code source<2) — **Topic:** Clean Architecture in Frontend Frameworks

**Pattern:** Layered Architecture (Domain, Application, Infrastructure, Presentation)

**Principles:**
- **Separation of Concerns**: Clear division between business logic (domain), use cases (application), external services (infrastructure), and UI (presentation).
  - *Example code*: `src/domain`, `src/application`, `src/infrastructure`, `src/presentation` (folder structure from referenced repos)

- **Dependency Rule**: Inner layers (domain) should not depend on outer layers (infrastructure).
  - *Example code*: Domain entities (`User.ts`) never import UI or API components (from [React + TypeScript Clean Architecture](https://github.com/bespoyasov/frontend-clean-architecture))

- **Single Responsibility**: Each layer/module has one reason to change.
  - *Example code*: `UserRepository` (infrastructure) only handles data access, not business logic (from [Express.js Clean Architecture](https://github.com/panagiop/node.js-clean-architecture))

**Example code:**
```typescript
// Domain layer (business rules)
export interface UserRepository {
  findById(id: string): Promise<User | null>;
}

// Infrastructure layer (external details)
export class PrismaUserRepository implements UserRepository {
  async findById(id: string): Promise<User | null> {
    return prisma.user.findUnique({ where: { id } });
  }
}
```

**Lesson:** Clean Architecture isolates core logic from frameworks/libraries, enabling testability and scalability.

**Verdict:** HIGH REUSABILITY for frontend/backend projects requiring maintainability.
